visors ca</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">n certify work as compliant on behalf of their business.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">All sole traders therefore must also be qualified supervisors. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">iii) the extent to which those carrying out electrical works, to which the Building Regulations apply, review or have their work revi</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ewed to ensure that it meets the requirements of the Regulations;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Approved Document P </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Electrical safety - Dwellings</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Section 3</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">paragraph 3.2</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">states “t</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">o verify that the design and installation of electrical work is adequate, and that installations </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">will be safe to use, maintain and alter, the electrical work should be inspected and tested in accordance with the procedures in BS 7671</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">BS 7671 </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Wiring Regulations</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">requires that all electrical installation work be inspected and tested to make sure that i</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">t complies with the installation and safety requirements in BS 7671</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Wiring Regulations</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. Installers are required to complete a BS 7671 </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Wiring Regulations</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">installation or minor works form which records the results of the inspection and testing. Certification</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> of compliance with the Building Regulations should not be given until the inspection and testing demonstrates that the work is safe. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Qualified supervisors have the competences to review the work carried out by their own business </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">before </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">certify</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> that i</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">t meets the requirements of the Building Regulations.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> The work carried out by qualified supervisors themselves is subject to checks by the scheme operators as in (iv) below.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Furthermore, the Approved Document P in </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Section 3</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">paragraph 3.1</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> directs that “f</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">r notifiable electrical installation work, one of the following three procedures must be used to certify that the work complies with the requirements set out in the Building Regulations.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0p