<span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">at least </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">every three years.  This period is granted to existing members who have a clean track record, based on factors such as inspection </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">outcomes, significant complaints and major changes in personnel.  Those m</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">embers without such a record are inspected on an annual basis</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">until they have such a record.  New members are inspected annually for the first two years following initial assessment to establish a clean track record.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Within these parameters</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> laid down by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the Department</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, scheme operators may choose to adopt more frequent inspection periods, where they consider that there is a need to go beyond the minimum requirements to ensure compliance with the Building Regulations</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> either generally for members of their scheme or targeted at particular members or class of members. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; paddin